## Gameplay Example: Boss Fight


// Boss entity with components:
// - HealthComponent (500 HP)
// - CombatComponent (strong attacker)
// - AI Component (behavior tree)
// - PhysicsComponent (can be knocked back)

// Player attacks:
// CombatSystem detects attack, raises DamageEvent(boss, 50 damage)
//   |
// HealthSystem listens, reduces health: 500 -> 450
//   |
// HealthComponent syncs to client (AutoNetworkedField)
//   |
// Client receives: Health changed to 450
//   |
// UI updates: Boss health bar shows 90%
//   |
// Next frame, AISystem checks: health < 300? Trigger phase 2
//   |
// Boss behavior changes: faster attacks, different pattern


All thanks to ECS pattern!

## Summary

- [bold]Entities[/bold] are unique IDs in the world
- [bold]Components[/bold] store data (no logic)
- [bold]Systems[/bold] contain logic (no data)
- [bold]Queries[/bold] find entities with specific components
- [bold]Events[/bold] let systems communicate without coupling

This flexibility lets you easily add features without touching existing code!
